</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SHARK! Nature's Masterpiece by R.D. Lawrence, illustrated by Gary Low 
(Chapters: $12.95; 177 pp.) . Sharks fascinate Lawrence, a well-known nature 
writer: Splendidly adapted to life in the sea, they've changed little over 
hundreds of millions of years. They don't get cancer and possess senses humans 
lack that detect microscopic electrical currents and chemical changes in water. 
Lawrence dismisses the media image of bloodthirsty killers, using his personal 
research to strengthen his argument that sharks are merely highly efficient 
carnivores. However, his descriptions of remaining underwater in a steel cage 
while trying to provoke a feeding frenzy may strike the casual reader as more 
foolhardy than scientific. 
</P>
</TEXT>
