<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LOVE IS HELL by Matt Groening (Pantheon: $9; unpaginated). This newly expanded 
anthology marks the 10th anniversary of Groening's delectably outrageous comic 
strip, "Life in Hell."Although Groening has never been a great draftsman, these 
early cartoons reveal how much his drawing has improved over the years. He was 
always wonderfully keen observer, with an ear for the mindless psychobabble 
that hangs over L.A. like intellectual smog. He's equally unkind to both 
genders, noting such unfortunately familiar types of couples as "I'm With 
Stupid x 2," "Mr. and Ms. Boredom" and "Sourballs vs. the World." 
</P>
</TEXT>
