<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR-STAR FILMS; 'REBEL WITHOUT A CAUSE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unless you were in high school or college when this classic of misunderstood 
youth was released in 1955, it may well be hard to comprehend James Dean's 
impact upon young people -- who really did want to be understood by their 
elders. Yet the electrifying sense of recognition we experienced in seeing Dean 
in this legendary Nicholas Ray film apparently has not diminished all that much 
for successor generations.And that is something that also could be said about 
Dean's appearances in his two other films, "Giant" and "East of Eden." With 
Natalie Wood (pictured) and Sal Mineo (TNT Tuesday at 5 p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
 Other four-star films airing this week: 
</P>
<P>
 Scrooge (1951) KNBC, Sunday, 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Howards End Disney, Sunday, 9 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 A Star Is Born (1954) TNT, Wednesday, 2:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Lawrence of Arabia TNT, Thursday, 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Stagecoach Bravo, Friday, 1:50 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Top Hat AMC, Saturday, 9:30 a.m. Kevin Thomas 
