RECORD RACK: IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Hochman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carla Olson, "Reap the Whirlwind," (***) Watermelon. The ex-Textones leader 
puts her husky, honeyed Texas voice to good use in duets with soul man Percy 
Sledge and Mark Lindsay (yes, that Mark Lindsay), spirited tracks that propel 
this earthy, rocking excursion. After years of "bubbling under" hit-dom, 
Olson's blues-informed pop has only gained heart -- perfect for fans of Bonnie 
Raitt's rougher side. Steve Hochman 
</P>
