GETTING THE POINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding art critic Christopher Knight's "Serrano's Critics Missed the Point" 
(Dec. 11), I was prepared to say that Knight missed the point, when lo, in the 
penultimate paragraph of this 1,500-word essay, there is a passing mention of 
controversy in Congress over funding of the "arts." 
</P>
<P>
 And there lies the point! It is typical of the overreach of centralized 
governmental involvement over the decades in nearly everything conceivable that 
we have taxpayers funding "artists" through the NEA.Regardless of the merits or 
otherwise of Serrano's "art," which Knight somewhat halfheartedly defends, as a 
taxpayer I do not relish having my pockets picked for this illegitimate 
purpose. 
</P>
<P>
 And while we're on the subject of Philistinism, who are the Philistines 
passing on the worthiness of these tax handouts? 
</P>
<P>
