<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENVIRONMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Notes about your surroundings 
</P>
<P>
 * Holiday Parking -- For those who want to try out new bikes, fall off in-line 
skates or take a post-meal stroll, county regional park facilities will be open 
today. However, the parks will be closed on Monday, the official county 
holiday. 
</P>
<P>
 * Craig Regional Park: This 124-acre park includes a fishing lake, three miles 
of hiking and biking trails and two playgrounds. Volleyball and basketball 
courts available. The park entrance is in Fullerton at 3300 N. State College 
Blvd., south of the Imperial Highway. 
</P>
<P>
 * Huntington Central Park: The park offers 300 acres of tree-covered hiking 
and biking trails and picnic areas. There's also a Frisbee golf course, 
horseshoe pits and a fitness course. The park is in Huntington Beach, with 
entrances on Edwards, Golden West and Gothard streets, and Slater and Talbert 
avenues. 
</P>
<P>
 * Irvine Regional Park: This is a 477-acre park with a lagoon and an array of 
hiking, biking and equestrian trails. You'll find volleyball courts, horseshoe 
pits and plenty of room for roaming. The park entrance is in Orange on Jamboree 
Road north of E. Chapman Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 * Laguna Niguel Regional Park: This 174-acre park is chock-full of fun. A 
large, stocked fishing lake is surrounded by hiking and biking trails. Also try 
out the four tennis courts. The park entrance is at 28241 La Paz Road, four 
miles west of Interstate 5. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mile Square Regional Park: This is a 340-acre park with more than 10 miles 
of hiking and bike trails. There are two fishing lakes, tennis and racquetball 
courts and several playgrounds. A favorite spot for motorized model airplanes 
and model car enthusiasts. The park entrance is in Fountain Valley on Euclid 
Avenue between Edinger and Warren avenues. 
</P>
<P>
 * William R. Mason Regional Park: This 95-acre park offers a nine-acre fishing 
lake that's also the local watering hole for model sail-boating. Other 
facilities include a Frisbee golf course, biking and hiking trails and 
playgrounds. The park is in Irvine at University and Culver drives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
