<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL: THE BOWLS; ROSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAV GLICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Nittany Lions, relocated in the Westin South Coast Plaza in Costa Mesa, 
are getting two days off after going through three two-a-day drills under Coach 
Joe Paterno at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The Big Ten champions, 112 strong, arrived in Southern California a week 
earlier than most Rose Bowl teams and spent their first five days at the Hilton 
Waterfront Resort in Huntington Beach before moving to Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 "We hadn't had but one real workout since our last game (Nov. 26) so we worked 
them pretty hard after we got here," Paterno said. "Now we're going to give 
them a rest because we don't want a bunch of heavy-legged kids for the game." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Five Penn State seniors have been elected captain for the Rose Bowl: 
quarterback Kerry Collins and center Bucky Greeley on offense, and linebackers 
Brian Gelzheiser and Willie Smith and tackle Vic Stewart on defense. SHAV GLICK 
</P>
