<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; HOLIDAY TREES TO BE RECYCLED AT 6 SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Starting Monday, residents who want to recycle their Christmas trees can do so 
at six Thousand Oaks locations. 
</P>
<P>
 For those who would rather keep the tree around for a while, the city will 
accept trees until Jan. 8. 
</P>
<P>
 The six locations are Borchard Park Service Center, 250 Reino Road, Newbury 
Park; Triunfo Community Park, 980 Aranmoor Ave., Westlake Village; Cal Lutheran 
University, Mount Clef Boulevard and Olsen Road; Home Depot, 500 N. Ventu Park 
Road; Park & Ride at Janss Road and the Moorpark Freeway, and Park & Ride, 
Rancho Road at the Moorpark Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 The city's public works department asks that trees be stripped of all 
ornaments and tinsel and that nails and stands be removed. The trees will be 
hauled to the Calabasas landfill and turned into mulch to be used throughout 
the Conejo Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, residents recycled more than 13,000 noble and Douglas firs and pine 
trees, Mayor Jaime Zukowski said. 
</P>
<P>
 "When you recycle your Christmas tree, you are helping the environment by 
keeping a valuable resource out of the landfill," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Trees that are flocked, painted or fire-proofed will not be accepted. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call the city's Recycling Hotline at 449-SAVE. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
