<P>
'ILLEGAL' LATINOS WERE INVALUABLE AFTER QUAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott Harris' column on home repairs (Dec. 15) certainly was right on the 
money for thousands of Valley homeowners, especially since the big quake a year 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
 I and all my friends just don't know what we would have done without all the 
"Juans" and "Pedros" waiting to be hired to do our moving, our home repair work 
and our yard cleanups.There were no union men waiting on the street corners to 
work, just our "illegal" Latinos, willing to give an honest day's work for $6 
to $10 per hour, depending on the skills involved. 
</P>
<P>
 I, for one, am thankful that the harsh provisions of Proposition 187 were not 
in place. Our recovery from the quake would have been delayed for years without 
the immigrant workers. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT E. GREEN 
