<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The six-team fields in each conference are set, but two division titles remain 
undetermined.  
</P>
<P>
 If Miami beats Detroit today, the Dolphins win the AFC East title; a loss or a 
tie gives the title to New England.  
</P>
<P>
 Detroit can win the NFC Central title with a victory and a loss or tie by 
Minnesota against San Francisco on Monday. If the Vikings win, the title is 
theirs. If both the Vikings and Lions lose, Green Bay wins the championship.  
</P>
<P>
 Pairings and times are expected to be announced Monday.  
</P>
<P>
 A look at who's in:  
</P>
<P>
 AFC 03,14,04,04 Team W L Pittsburgh* 12 4 San Diego* 11 5 Cleveland 11 5 New 
England* 10 6 Miami 9 6 Kansas City 9 7 NFC 03,16,04,04 Team W L San Francisco* 
13 2 Dallas* 12 4 Minnesota 9 6 Detroit 9 6 Green Bay 9 7 Chicago 9 7 * 
Division leaders  
</P>
