<HEADLINE>
<P>
ISRAELIS KILL 1 LEBANESE, HURT 4 OTHERS, SOURCES SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Israeli soldiers shot and killed a Lebanese bird hunter and wounded four 
others in Israeli-held southern Lebanon on Saturday, apparently mistaking them 
for guerrillas, security sources said. 
</P>
<P>
 An Israeli spotted the five men armed with hunting rifles in woods near the 
southeastern town of Hasbayya and opened fire with automatic weapons, the 
sources said on condition of anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
 The sources in Marjayoun said the Israelis must have mistook the hunters for 
Muslim fundamentalist guerrillas. 
</P>
<P>
 The Israeli army confirmed in a statement that a Lebanese civilian was killed 
and three injured. It said soldiers fired on "suspicious figures in a 
prohibited area." 
</P>
<P>
 Israeli soldiers and the Israeli-backed South Lebanon Army frequently shoot at 
civilians who wander in the fields of southern Lebanon without clearance. 
</P>
<P>
 The Israelis and their Lebanese allies have been particularly edgy following 
heavy clashes with Muslim guerrillas. 
</P>
<P>
 On Friday, two Israeli soldiers were killed and seven wounded in an attack 
that touched off daylong battles. Sporadic exchanges were reported Saturday. 
</P>
