<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN CROSSING STREET STRUCK, KILLED BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A pedestrian was killed Christmas Eve when a suspected drunken driver careened 
through an intersection at high speed, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A 22-year-old Huntington Beach man, whose name was not released Saturday night 
pending notification of his family, was struck and killed as he crossed Ellis 
Avenue at Delaware Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Ed Deuel said the man was thrown more than 200 feet. The accident 
happened at 6:10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police the driver, identified as Paul J. Gronley of Huntington 
Beach, ran a stop sign at 80 m.p.h., Deuel said. The speed limit at the 
intersection is 35 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
 Gronley, 41, was arrested on suspicion of drunken driving and vehicular 
manslaughter and was being held in the city jail on $50,000 bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122594-0283 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 111415 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 25, 1994, Sunday, Valley Edition 
</P>
