<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTAGE CUTS POWER TO 1,600 HOMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 1,600 homes lost Christmas tree lights and all their other electrical 
power in Saturday night's heavy downpour, according to officials with the 
Department of Water and Power. 
</P>
<P>
 In Encino, about 800 homes lost power just after 6 p.m. In West Hills, another 
800 lost power about 7 p.m. Neither area had power restored as of 9:30 p.m., 
said DWP spokeswoman Debra Sass. 
</P>
<P>
 Sass said crews were unsure what caused the outage, although they believed the 
problem to be weather-related. Correcting the problem was expected to take 
several hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122594-0291 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 111423 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
